</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F0BFF9CFF26FE85FDCAFEA3" blockId="62.[151,1436,150,429]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
Habitat. Infralittoral species known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F0BFF9CFD75FE84FD1DFEFC" box="[660,765,258,285]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.025" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.05" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" unit="m" value="10.25" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–20 m</quantity>
depth on very diverse hard or mixed bottoms (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFAE0FE85FA77FEFC" author="Patzner, R. A." box="[1281,1431,259,285]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
; P. Louisy unpublished observation).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F0BFF9CFF26FECDFD0FFE4C" blockId="62.[151,1436,150,429]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
Geographic distribution. The whole of the Mediterranean (Miller 1986), Black Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFB8DFECDFA86FE84" author="Engin, S. &amp; Seyhan, K." box="[1132,1382,331,357]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" pagination="111 - 118" refId="ref53766" refString="Engin, S. &amp; Seyhan, K. (2009) Biological characteristics of rock goby Gobius paganellus in the South eastern Black Sea. Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 39, 111 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIP 2009.39.2.05" type="journal article" year="2009">Engin &amp; Seyhan 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and Eastern Atlantic from 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F0BFF9CFE6EFEE9FDC2FE68" box="[399,546,367,393]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Great Britain</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F0BFF9CFDA7FEE9FD7FFE68" box="[582,671,367,393]" name="Senegal" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Senegal</collectingCountry>
(Miller 1986), including the Azores (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFBA0FEE9FAEFFE68" author="Santos, R. S. &amp; Porteiro, F. M. &amp; Barreiros, J. P." box="[1089,1295,367,393]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 244" refId="ref64282" refString="Santos, R. S., Porteiro, F. M. &amp; Barreiros, J. P. (1997) Marine fishes of the Azores: annotated checklist and bibliography. Bulletin of the University of Azores, Supplement 1, 1 - 244." type="journal article" year="1997">
Santos 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F0BFF9CFB75FEE9FB25FE68" box="[1172,1221,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">et al</emphasis>
. 1997
</bibRefCitation>
), the Canary Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFF14FE15FE95FE4C" author="Wirtz, P." box="[245,373,403,429]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" refId="ref66060" refString="Wirtz, P. (1994) Underwater Guide. Fish of Madeira, Canary Islands and Azores. Verlag Stephanie Naglschmid, Stuttgart, 126 pp." type="book" year="1994">Wirtz 1994</bibRefCitation>
) and Madeira (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0BFF9CFDC1FE15FD03FE4C" author="Wirtz, P. &amp; Fricke, R. &amp; Biscoito, M. J." box="[544,739,403,429]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref66145" refString="Wirtz, P., Fricke, R. &amp; Biscoito, M. J. (2008) The coastal fishes of Madeira Island - new records and an annotated check-list. Zootaxa, 1715 (1), 1 - 26. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1715.1.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Wirtz 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F0BFF9CFD86FE15FD79FE4C" box="[615,665,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
